The paper deals with the design of random modulation preintegration systems for analog to information conversion of sparse and localized signals. This topic falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on signal processing and information theory, cs.IT and cs.SP are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.SI.
